  "text": "As breast cancer, compared with other cancers affecting women, is associated with alcohol consumption, a related study [CITATION_1] investigated the effect of alcohol exposure (100 mM for 48 h) on the growth regulation in T47D breast cancer cells. The researchers used 2D electrophoresis and matrix assisted laser desorption, time of flight (MALDI-ToF) MS to evaluate changes in protein expression in addition to various other techniques. Results showed 14 downregulated and 8 upregulated proteins. The increased expression of c-ros receptor tyrosine kinase (ROS1) was confirmed by western blotting. This study demonstrated the relationship between alcohol and cell proliferation associated with activation of the MAPK pathway by ROS1 protein.",
